laboratory_examinations.findings: Dilated, fluid-filled appendix, measuring up to 9 mm in diameter. Normal liver with homogeneous enhancement, no intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation. Normal gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and kidneys with prompt excretion of IV contrast bilaterally. No hydronephrosis, free fluid, or air in the intra-abdominal cavity. Normal fecal loading in the colon, normal uterus and bilateral follicular activity in the adnexae, moderately distended urinary bladder.
